I am writing to request that Community Colleges be exempt of the 5 % additional cut imposed by Executive Order 21. 
As the Governor well knows, Community Colleges are a vital part of preparing ones self for the future. We are on ground level meeting students face to face.   We are charged with the next step in education, teaching the fundamentals of real world work.  We must continue teaching the fundamentals. As in football, fundamentals are blocking and tackling. Until we embrace this then the rest gets lost in the shuffle.  The same as in life, unless the fundamentals are taught repeatedly and embraced by the students they are at risk of losing much of their potential. These fundamentals and  education will remain with students the rest of their life.

We provide opportunities to most students who are living on the lower end of the economic scale.   Many would never see the college classroom, nor would they reach their potential.  We are their life support, their highway to higher education, their hope to rise above their present status and their dream for a better life.
As a trustee of Gaston College I see the students and I see the hope.  I am on one of our campuses almost every week and I see the students knowing full well that many would not be in higher education if it were not for our college.  

Community Colleges have a story to tell, all 58 of us and I am requesting that you as the Governor recognize this meaningful request when considering the exemption as described in Executive Order 21.  This could make a significant difference in the life of many students.

We are making a difference and with your help this difference will grow.

Thank you,

